00:00:17.530 --> 00:00:21.220 align:middle line:84%
>> It seems to me what I've
been speaking to is the issue

00:00:21.220 --> 00:00:26.450 align:middle line:84%
of the use of psychedelics for
inner work, for spiritual work.

00:00:26.450 --> 00:00:29.480 align:middle line:84%
There are a couple of things
I should point out about that.

00:00:29.480 --> 00:00:34.910 align:middle line:10%
One is that a lot of the reason
we used psychedelics because

00:00:34.910 --> 00:00:39.230 align:middle line:10%
of the monolithic quality of the
belief systems of the culture

00:00:39.230 --> 00:00:44.090 align:middle line:10%
are no longer the way it is,
that relative reality, which

00:00:44.090 --> 00:00:49.020 align:middle line:10%
was awakened '50s and
'60s and came back in,

00:00:49.020 --> 00:00:52.970 align:middle line:10%
but there was a lot of stuff
that forced relative reality

00:00:52.970 --> 00:00:54.260 align:middle line:10%
as consciousness.

00:00:54.260 --> 00:00:57.980 align:middle line:84%
And that has mainstreamed
in the society.

00:00:57.980 --> 00:00:59.780 align:middle line:84%
I'll pick up a
